ds3CfgXmitLineBuildOut.name: ds3CfgXmitLineBuildOut
ds3CfgXmitLineBuildOut.description: This object is used to configure the amount of attenuation that is to be applied to the DS3 transmit signal in order to control cross-talk, etc. The settings are for distances of 0-225 feet or 226 to 450 feet. Default=225(1)

ds3CfgMonitorPortSource.name: ds3CfgMonitorPortSource
ds3CfgMonitorPortSource.description: This object is for designation of monitor port DS1 source. Default=spanLine1(1).

ds3CurrentTable.name: ds3CurrentTable
ds3CurrentTable.description: This table contains various statistics being collected for the current 15 minute interval.

ds3CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 current table.

ds3CurrentIndex.name: ds3CurrentIndex
ds3CurrentIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS3 interface to which this entry is applicable.

ds3CurrentFCPs.name: ds3CurrentFCPs
ds3CurrentFCPs.description: This object indicates near end path failure count. The count of LOF or AIS events.

ds3CurrentFCCPs.name: ds3CurrentFCCPs
ds3CurrentFCCPs.description: This object indicates far end path failure count. The count of Remote Alarm Indication (RAI) events.

ds3CurrentSESLs.name: ds3CurrentSESLs
ds3CurrentSESLs.description: The object is the counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds on the line.

ds3CurrentUASCPs.name: ds3CurrentUASCPs
ds3CurrentUASCPs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds for the C-bit parity application.

ds3IntervalTable.name: ds3IntervalTable
ds3IntervalTable.description: The DS3 Interval Table contains various statistics collected by each DS3 Interface over the previous 24 hours of operation. The past 24 hours are broken into 96 completed 15 minute intervals. Each row in this table represents one such interval (identified by ds3IntervalNumber) and for one specific interface (identified by ds3IntervalIndex).

ds3IntervalEntry.name: ds3IntervalEntry
ds3IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Interval Table.

ds3IntervalIndex.name: ds3IntervalIndex
ds3IntervalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS3 interface to which this entry is applicable.

ds3IntervalNumber.name: ds3IntervalNumber
ds3IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the 15 minutes interval completes 23 hours and 45 minutes prior to interval 1.

ds3IntervalSESLs.name: ds3IntervalSESLs
ds3IntervalSESLs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds on the line in the previous 15 minute interval.

ds3IntervalCVCPs.name: ds3IntervalCVCPs
ds3IntervalCVCPs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of near-end path code violations for the C-bit parity application in the previous 15 minute interval.

ds3IntervalUASCPs.name: ds3IntervalUASCPs
ds3IntervalUASCPs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds for the C-bit parity application in the previous 15 minute interval.

ds3TotalTable.name: ds3TotalTable
ds3TotalTable.description: The DS3 Total Table contains the cumulative sum of the various statics for the 24 hour period preceding the current interval.

ds3TotalEntry.name: ds3TotalEntry
ds3TotalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Total Table.

ds3TotalIndex.name: ds3TotalIndex
ds3TotalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS3 interface to which this entry is applicable.

ds3TotalSESLs.name: ds3TotalSESLs
ds3TotalSESLs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds on the line in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 intervals count as 0.

ds3TotalCVCPs.name: ds3TotalCVCPs
ds3TotalCVCPs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of near-end path code violations for the C-bit parity application in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

ds3TotalUASCPs.name: ds3TotalUASCPs
ds3TotalUASCPs.description: This object is the counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds for the C-bit parity application in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.
